list.abstract: grocery（英 [ˈɡrəʊsəri]，美 [ˈɡroʊsəri]），英语单词，名词，意思为食品杂货店；食品杂货业；食品杂货。短语搭配有grocery store（杂货店；小卖部；食品杂货铺），例句为“But there is plenty of decent food in the grocery stores.（但是杂货店里有很多像样的食物）”。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, we have beautiful grocery stores here in North Korea.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们大朝鲜还是有好的杂货店的。

yingyinNormal.en: I can believe that. It looks like you hit the grocery store pretty often.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我信，听起来你常去杂货店。

yingyinNormal.en: You know what? That's a great idea, you're right. We're on our way to the grocery.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还真是。这是个好主意，你说得对。我们去趟杂货店。

yingyinNormal.en: I see. Well, yeah, I mean, I did see a fat kid and a really nice-looking grocery store.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，这样啊，我见到个营养过剩的和一个不错的杂货店。

yingyinNormal.en: If you'd rather cook at home, you can shop at over 3,000 supermarket chains and hundreds of thousands of independent grocery stores in the U.S..
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你更喜欢在家自己做饭，在美国，你能在超过3000家连锁超市以及成百上千家杂货店里，买到需要的食材。

yingyinNormal.en: Remarkable. Diamonds, crystallized carbon. Every day, people go to the grocery store and come home with sacks full of carbon in the form of charcoal briquettes that they toss in their barbeques and set on fire.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真神奇，钻石不过就是结晶状的碳而已，人们每天去杂货店买回家的也是碳，只不过是被人丢进烤炉当火源的炭块。

yingyinNormal.en: You're in line at the grocery store when, uh oh, someone sneezes on you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在超市里排队，哦，不妙，有个人朝你打了个喷嚏。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, wow! It's a grocery store. Looks like the Whole Foods around the corner from my place.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哇，一个百货店，这就像我家附近的全食食品店。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't. He broke up with me. Oh, no. He's moving to Africa. Because they need grocery models in Africa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不行，他跟我分手了。不是吧。他要搬去非洲，因为非洲的超市需要模特。

yingyinNormal.en: Going to the grocery store, driving you to the doctor. If you're not in a hurry, I can dig you a koi pond.
yingyinNormal.zh: 帮忙去超市买菜，开车载你去看医生。如果不着急，我可以帮忙你挖个锦鲤池。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, and none of these stupid grocery questions, real personal questions. Yeah. And the winner gets a hundred bucks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猜东西没挑战性，这次要问切身问题，赌一百块。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, okay, then you let me go grocery shopping. No problem. I'm not done yet. And I buy laundry detergent, but it's not the one with the easy-pour spout.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你让我去买日常用品，我买了洗衣粉。没问题。我还没说完，但是是不容易倒出来的那种。

yingyinNormal.en: Everyone! Just think. Your neighbor, the grocery store manager, that chicken, right there! Everyone in this city gets a shot at being a star live on my stage.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有人看！你难道忘了，你的邻居，那个开杂货铺的，那个公鸡叫什么？对，哦对，就是他，我要让每个普通人都有机会成为明星，在我的舞台上表演。

yingyinNormal.en: You mean whenever Monica and Chandler where like you know, doing laundry or going grocery shopping or all that time Monica spent on the phone with sad Linda from camp.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是说每次莫妮卡和钱德去洗衣服或买东西或她每次跟伤心的琳达讲电话。

sense_info_list.en: items of food sold in a grocery store

examination_example.sentence: But there is plenty of decent food in the <highlight>grocery</highlight> stores.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是杂货店里有很多像样的食物。

examination_example.sentence: The common prescription is to primarily shop the <highlight>grocery</highlight> store, since that's where fresh produce, meat and seafood, and dairy are.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通常的做法是主要在杂货店购物，因为那里有新鲜农产品、肉类、海鲜和乳制品。

examination_example.sentence: You don't have to hit the <highlight>grocery</highlight> store daily, nor do you need an abundance of skill.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你不必每天去杂货店，也不需要丰富的技能。

examination_example.sentence: The ads criticized the measure, characterizing it as a "<highlight>grocery</highlight> tax".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 广告批评了这项措施，称其为“杂货税”。

examination_example.sentence: The center's ‘ Shop with Your Doc program sends doctors to the <highlight>grocery</highlight> store to meet with any patients who sign up for the service, plus any other shoppers who happen to be around with questions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该中心的“与你的医生一起购物”项目可将医生带到杂货店与任何报名参加该服务的病人见面，及碰巧遇到问题的其他购物者会面。
